To write the condition 
    i < lim-1 && (c = getchar()) != '\n' && c != EOF
not using && or ||: 

We keep the i < lim-1 in the for loop condition and wrap the original for loop body with the followings: 
    if ((c = getchar()) != '\n') {
        if (c != EOF) {
            // the original for loop body
        }
    }